#. <section class="sutta" id="sn36.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Sagāthāvagga"
msgstr "1. With Verses"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn36.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Phassamūlakasutta"
msgstr "10. Rooted in Contact"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.215"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, vedanā phassajā phassamūlakā phassanidānā "
"phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these three feelings are born, rooted, sourced, and conditioned "
"by contact."

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.2"
msgid "Katamā tisso?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.3"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā."
msgstr "Pleasant, painful, and neutral feeling."

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.4"
msgid "Sukhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhā vedanā."
msgstr ""
"Pleasant feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as pleasant."

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.5"
msgid ""
"Tasseva sukhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā, yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"sukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā sukhā vedanā, sā nirujjhati, sā "
"vūpasammati."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as pleasant, the "
"corresponding pleasant feeling ceases and stops."

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.6"
msgid "Dukkhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhā vedanā."
msgstr ""
"Painful feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as painful."

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.7"
msgid ""
"Tasseva dukkhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā, yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"dukkhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā dukkhā vedanā, sā nirujjhati, sā "
"vūpasammati."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as painful, the "
"corresponding painful feeling ceases and stops."

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.8"
msgid ""
"Adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati adukkhamasukhā "
"vedanā."
msgstr ""
"Neutral feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as neutral."

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.9"
msgid ""
"Tasseva adukkhamasukhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā, yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā adukkhamasukhā vedanā, sā "
"nirujjhati, sā vūpasammati."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as neutral, the "
"corresponding neutral feeling ceases and stops."

#. VAR: saṅghaṭṭanasamodhānā → saṅkhattā tassa samodānā (s1, s2, km) | saṅghaṭṭā tassa samodhānā (s3) | saṅghattā tassa samodhānā (mr)
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.10"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dvinnaṃ kaṭṭhānaṃ saṅghaṭṭanasamodhānā usmā jāyati, "
"tejo abhinibbattati. Tesaṃyeva kaṭṭhānaṃ nānābhāvā vinikkhepā, yā tajjā "
"usmā, sā nirujjhati, sā vūpasammati."
msgstr ""
"When you rub two sticks together, heat is generated and fire is produced. "
"But when you part the sticks and lay them aside, any corresponding heat "
"ceases and stops."

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.11"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, imā tisso vedanā phassajā phassamūlakā phassanidānā "
"phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, these three feelings are born, rooted, sourced, and "
"conditioned by contact."

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.12"
msgid "Tajjaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca tajjā vedanā uppajjanti."
msgstr "The appropriate feeling arises dependent on the corresponding contact."

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.13"
msgid "Tajjassa phassassa nirodhā tajjā vedanā nirujjhantī”ti."
msgstr "When the corresponding contact ceases, the appropriate feeling ceases.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.14"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.15"
msgid "Vedanāsaṃyuttassa sagāthāvaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.10:2.1"
msgid "Samādhi sukhaṃ pahānena,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.10:2.2"
msgid "pātālaṃ daṭṭhabbena ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.10:2.3"
msgid "Sallena ceva gelaññā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.10:2.4"
msgid "anicca phassamūlakāti."
msgstr ""
